01:12:47,092 --> 01:12:48,821
<i>(SINGING) Pack</i>

911
01:12:49,961 --> 01:12:52,691
<i>And get dressed</i>

912
01:12:54,499 --> 01:13:01,268
<i>Before your father hears us</i>

913
01:13:02,240 --> 01:13:04,708
<i>Before</i>

914
01:13:05,610 --> 01:13:08,010
<i>All hell</i>

915
01:13:09,981 --> 01:13:13,677
<i>Breaks loose</i>

916
01:13:38,876 --> 01:13:41,003
I paid Porter $200,

917
01:13:43,180 --> 01:13:45,341
and he did some research.

918
01:13:45,449 --> 01:13:47,713
I let my family down.

919
01:13:47,714 --> 01:13:50,386
I'm really ashamed about this,

920
01:13:50,387 --> 01:13:53,618
and I just want to put it behind me
as soon as possible.

921
01:14:01,532 --> 01:14:05,263
<i>MASTER PO: (ON TV) Grasshopper,
are you fishing in our lily pond?</i>

922
01:14:05,402 --> 01:14:07,427
MEREDITH: Come on. Let's go see your dad.

923
01:14:10,140 --> 01:14:12,004
- I'm not going.
- Fine.

924
01:14:12,308 --> 01:14:16,218
If you don't want to go, then don't go.
But you're not just going to sleep all day.

925
01:14:17,380 --> 01:14:18,430
Come on.

926
01:14:19,315 --> 01:14:21,180
Come on, Porter. Let's go. Get up!

927
01:14:21,181 --> 01:14:22,317
- For Christ's sake.
- Stop!

928
01:14:22,318 --> 01:14:24,286
- HENRY: Are we going?
- Stop! Stop!

929
01:14:24,887 --> 01:14:25,937
Yes.

930
01:14:27,023 --> 01:14:28,115
Fine.

931
01:14:30,827 --> 01:14:33,455
Just do something, all right?

932
01:14:33,529 --> 01:14:36,726
Go outside, take a walk, steal a car.
I don't care.

933
01:14:36,799 --> 01:14:39,825
I just don't want to find you back in bed
when I get home.

934
01:14:51,447 --> 01:14:53,210
NURSE: Your family's here.

935
01:15:06,762 --> 01:15:08,753
It's okay. Go on.

936
01:15:14,436 --> 01:15:16,563
Hey, little fella. How are you?

937
01:15:17,339 --> 01:15:18,431
Good.

938
01:15:19,074 --> 01:15:20,200
What's that?

939
01:15:21,042 --> 01:15:23,533
- It's a brain.
- Wow. It's a brain!

940
01:15:24,279 --> 01:15:26,304
Mom says yours got broken.

941
01:15:26,715 --> 01:15:28,740
This will come in handy.

942
01:15:28,850 --> 01:15:32,752
So, are you crazy?

943
01:15:34,222 --> 01:15:36,213
Maybe.

944
01:15:36,324 --> 01:15:37,552
We're working on it.

945
01:15:38,526 --> 01:15:41,393
Does that mean you can come home?

946
01:15:41,463 --> 01:15:42,783
We're working on that, too.

947
01:15:43,565 --> 01:15:44,945
Hey, where's your brother?

948
01:15:45,901 --> 01:15:49,428
Probably sleeping. It's all he does.

949
01:15:52,274 --> 01:15:53,639
Come here.

950
01:15:54,576 --> 01:15:57,306
Come here! I'll bite you on your ear!

951
01:16:27,441 --> 01:16:28,491
(CELL PHONE BUZZES)

952
01:16:49,029 --> 01:16:50,291
Wow.

953
01:16:51,699 --> 01:16:53,929
I must have sent you 15 texts.

954
01:16:54,735 --> 01:16:56,566
I'd given up on you.

955
01:16:58,072 --> 01:17:02,133
Well, that makes two of us.

956
01:17:03,544 --> 01:17:07,344
You were right.
I guess I had some stuff to say.

957
01:17:09,783 --> 01:17:12,273
Apparently, a lot of stuff.

958
01:17:14,387 --> 01:17:17,845
Anyway, now you know what's on my mind,
so you can write my speech.

959
01:17:17,991 --> 01:17:19,822
No.

960
01:17:19,926 --> 01:17:22,554
I think I'm officially out of that business.

961
01:17:22,729 --> 01:17:24,128
You owe me.

962
01:17:27,433 --> 01:17:29,594
You made this for me.

963
01:17:30,269 --> 01:17:32,032
Yesterday.

964
01:17:32,772 --> 01:17:34,399
How come?

965
01:17:34,540 --> 01:17:37,070
Because there's more
that belongs on a wall than,

966
01:17:38,177 --> 01:17:40,543
"Norah has a dead brother."

967
01:17:42,715 --> 01:17:44,114
Even if it is a big mess.

968
01:17:45,818 --> 01:17:47,115
It's amazing.

969
01:17:49,055 --> 01:17:53,014
Funny. I think it's a mess,
and you think it's amazing.

970
01:17:53,092 --> 01:17:55,862
And I think you're amazing,
and you think you're a mess.

971
01:17:57,864 --> 01:18:01,425
You know what?
I don't want to think anymore.

972
01:18:06,572 --> 01:18:09,006
You still owe me a speech.

973
01:18:09,742 --> 01:18:11,868
Just make sure it sounds like me.

974
01:18:19,184 --> 01:18:23,985
So, do I just sit here writing
and get arrested again?

975
01:18:24,056 --> 01:18:26,616
No, take it with you, dummy.

976
01:18:27,025 --> 01:18:29,960
Take it with me?

977
01:19:15,239 --> 01:19:18,333
<i>PORTER: Good afternoon,
graduates, dead poets,</i>

978
01:19:18,476 --> 01:19:22,708
<i>painters, future Einsteins,
and all those in between.</i>

979
01:19:23,214 --> 01:19:26,547
<i>Today I'm here to warn you
that you are being lied to.</i>

980
01:19:26,684 --> 01:19:31,553
<i>Our parents, our teachers, our doctors
have lied to us.</i>

981
01:19:31,655 --> 01:19:36,752
<i>And it's the exact same lie.
The same six words,</i>

982
01:19:36,861 --> 01:19:39,329
<i>"Everything is going to be okay."</i>

983
01:19:41,365 --> 01:19:43,128
<i>But what if it isn't?</i>

984
01:19:43,129 --> 01:19:47,303
<i>What if some of human experience
is just something you inherit,</i>

985
01:19:47,304 --> 01:19:50,102
<i>like curly hair or blue eyes?</i>

986
01:19:50,174 --> 01:19:54,838
<i>What if pain is just in your DNA
and tragedy is your birthright?</i>

987
01:19:56,280 --> 01:19:57,330
<i>Or what if...</i>

988
01:19:57,331 --> 01:20:00,283
<i>NORAH: "Or what if sometimes..."
PORTER: ...sometimes...</i>

989
01:20:00,284 --> 01:20:03,151
"...right out of the blue,
when you least expect it,

990
01:20:04,021 --> 01:20:06,455
"shit just happens?

991
01:20:08,759 --> 01:20:10,556
"Shit just happens."

992
01:20:11,094 --> 01:20:15,564
Okay, I'm sure, right now,
you're all thinking,

993
01:20:15,565 --> 01:20:18,695
"Man, this is the darkest graduation speech
I've ever heard."

994
01:20:19,068 --> 01:20:22,037
And it is.
I agree with you, but I didn't write it.

995
01:20:26,409 --> 01:20:31,506
I've spent so much time
waiting for this lie to come true

996
01:20:31,581 --> 01:20:35,244
that I finally paid someone
to tell the truth for me.

997
01:20:38,688 --> 01:20:40,212
I'm not okay.

998
01:20:40,757 --> 01:20:42,224
Not at all.

999
01:20:44,627 --> 01:20:46,891
The truth is,

1000
01:20:46,963 --> 01:20:49,227
I'm missing something,

1001
01:20:50,934 --> 01:20:52,458
the thing I loved the most,

1002
01:20:53,736 --> 01:20:56,705
the face I wish
were in the front row right now.

1003
01:20:59,075 --> 01:21:01,771
The brother I'll never get back.

1004
01:21:06,883 --> 01:21:08,942
So what do I do with that?

1005
01:21:12,588 --> 01:21:14,647
What do any of us do,

1006
01:21:15,591 --> 01:21:17,582
besides lie?

1007
01:21:20,896 --> 01:21:23,023
This is what I believe.

1008
01:21:26,635 --> 01:21:31,368
Right now, in this auditorium,
there is someone who is with you.

1009
01:21:31,440 --> 01:21:35,809
Someone who is willing to pick you up,
dust you off,

1010
01:21:35,877 --> 01:21:37,139
kiss you, forgive you,

1011
01:21:38,113 --> 01:21:41,412
put up with you, wait for you, carry you,

1012
01:21:41,783 --> 01:21:43,182
<i>love you.</i>

1013
01:21:45,520 --> 01:21:48,353
<i>So, while everything
may not always be okay,</i>

1014
01:21:49,291 --> 01:21:51,452
<i>one thing I know is true.</i>

1015
01:21:53,128 --> 01:21:55,528
<i>You do not have to be alone.</i>

1016
01:22:38,005 --> 01:22:40,473
I didn't think you'd come.

1017
01:22:40,741 --> 01:22:43,107
I didn't think I would, either.

1018
01:22:50,918 --> 01:22:52,783
I'm just glad you're still here.

1019
01:22:54,655 --> 01:22:56,520
Yeah, most of me, anyway.

1020
01:22:57,124 --> 01:22:58,648
Yeah.

1021
01:23:03,798 --> 01:23:05,766
You know, when I was a little kid,

1022
01:23:06,267 --> 01:23:09,668
man, all I ever wanted was to be like you.

1023
01:23:12,740 --> 01:23:14,206
Then I got older,

1024
01:23:16,876 --> 01:23:19,640
and I just wanted to be anybody else.

1025
01:23:26,386 --> 01:23:27,436
And now?

1026
01:23:33,860 --> 01:23:34,952
Dad.

1027
01:24:32,651 --> 01:24:35,841
<i>WALTER: (AS WALTER)
This is a picture of Walter Black,</i>

1028
01:24:36,822 --> 01:24:39,450
<i>who had to become a beaver,</i>

1029
01:24:39,525 --> 01:24:41,993
<i>who had to become a father,</i>

1030
01:24:43,295 --> 01:24:48,790
<i>so that, one day, this might
just be a picture of Walter Black.</i>



